** Dependancies **
------------------
None


** Compiling **
---------------
If included in main.cpp:
  g++ -c main.cpp -I ~/workspace
  g++ main.o -o main -L ~/workspace/Harmony/ -lharmony-math

i.e. C++14 & in Harmony's libharmony-math.a


** READ **
----------

This is an integer that can be arbitrarily large (see TO DO for caviat), so represents ZZ space

There is no division or modulus operators at the moment


** Interface **
---------------

Construction :
   Integer name{}            - constructs an Integer with value 0
   Integer name(int number)  - constructs an Integer from an integral type
   Integer name(string s)    - constructs an Integer corresponding to passed string

length() : gives length of the number in digits (not including negative sign)

operators allowed : + , - , * , += , -= , *= , ++ (both sides) , -- (both sides)
                    == , != , < , > , <= , >= , << (streaming)
